“I think I speak for every business owner who’s applied for these loans but haven’t been approved,” Utah small business owner Tricia Bennion said.
The Paycheck Protection Program provides federally guaranteed loans to eligible small businesses in amounts up to $10 million and may be partially forgivable.
Herbert noted that small businesses, those with 500 or fewer employees, make up about 90% of all businesses in Utah and, of those companies, about half have less than 50 employees.
“Small businesses are the backbone of the Utah economy,” Herbert said.